#HELPS
-1 'RACE HELP' 'RACE' 'RACES'~
Shadows Reborn has the following races for player characters:

Your character may be one of a variety of races. Each race has a different
set of characteristics: starting attributes, maximum values attributes can be
trained to, intrinsic abilities, and so on. The more exotic races cost
additional creation points (cps) which will increase the experience you need
to gain a level.  

NOTE: If you are an experienced mudder, you may wish to choose
an ORC race as they have a different homeland then Midgaard. 
 
The following races are available (type help race, eg. 'help dwarf', for more
information on a specific race):
 
- Human       average in all regards, no special abilities, no cp cost
- Elf         nimble and intelligent, make good mages or thieves, 5 cps
- Dwarf       strong and sturdy, make good warriors or clerics, 8 cps
- Giant       gigantic, tough creatures, make good warriors, 6 cps
- Cyborg      man-made constructs, make good warriors or thieves, 8 cps
- Wolfen      sapient canines, make good warriors or thieves, 7 cps
- Halfling    small, quick, gnome-like humanoids, 5 cps
- Ogre        brutish, strong...really hairy individuals, 7 cps
- Minotaur    half man, half sumpin' else...really nasty and strong, 9 cps
- Pixie       effite little woodland creatures with bite, 8 cps
- Gargoyle    very strong, extremely fugly, very bad temper, 10 cps
- Centaur     fleet of foot, very agile and graceful, 10 cps
 
ORCAN RACES:
 
- Orc          violent, deadly, but the most average of all, no cps cost
- Troll        huge green creatures, mommy didn't love them, 9 cps
- Uruk-hai     half-breed bad-ass orcs that would eat mamma for lunch, 10 cps
- Hobgoblin    twisted goblins built for war and destruction, 4 cps
- Drow         dark, cute, and sneaky as quicksilver..., 6 cps
- Kobold       mini-werewolves, really nasty and sneaky, 6 cps
- Stalker      the perfect assassins, stealth warriors, 12 cps
- Naga         Snake like creature, likes to hiss and use it's tail, 6 cp
- Felar        Cat-like, shadow-dwellers, like human catnip, 7 cps
- Kenku       bird like creatures, like to scratch eyes out, 7 cps
- Illithid     mysterious creatures...no one knows what they do, 14 cps
- Lizardmen    Quickly regenerating creatures that aren't silky-smooth, 8 cps
 
'help race statistics' will give you an overview of each race's max stats.


Different races have different starting statistics, and also different
stat maximums for magic items and training.

Creation points increase the amount of experience it takes to gain a level.
For more information, see the help files for each race (i.e. 'help dwarf')
~

