0 HUMAN~
Humans are the most common race in the world, and make up the majority of
adventurers. Although they have no special talents like the other races,
they are more versitile, being skilled in all four classes. Humans may
also train their primary stat higher than any other race, and are able to
gain more benefit from magical devices.

Favored Class: All

Natural Ability: Staves, Scrolls, Wands, Potions and Pills all activate as if they
were three levels higher, all classes are 'favored' classes.

*************************************
~

0 ELF ELVES~
Elves are slightly taller than humans, but have a much lighter build.  They
lack the strength and stamina of the other races, but are far more agile,
both in body and mind.  Elves are superb mages and thieves, but have at
best fair talent as warriors or priests.

Elves resist charm spells most effectively, due to their magical nature.
However, they are burned by the touch of iron, and so are barred from the
use of iron or steel in their adventuring careers.  Elves are notoriously 
hard to spot, and so elven warriors and thieves recieve the sneak and hiding
automatically. They may see in the dark with infravision.

Favored Class: Mage

Natural Ability: Sneak and Hide at level 1

*************************************
~

0 DWARF DWARVES~
Dwarves are short, stocky demi-humans, known for foul temper and great
stamina.  Dwarves have high strength and constitution, but poor dexterity.
They are not as smart as humans, but are usually wiser due to their long 
lifespans.  Dwarves make excellent fighters and priests, but are very poor
mages or thieves.  

Dwarves are very resistant to poison and disease, but cannot swim, and so
are very vulnerable to drowning.  They recieve the berserk skill for free
(if warriors), and can see in the dark with infravision.

Favored Class: Cleric and Warrior

Natural Ability: Headbutt

*************************************
~

0 VERBEEG~
Verbeeg are the largest of the races, ranging from 9-12 feet in height.  They
are stronger than any other race, and almost as durable as the dwarves.  
They aren't too bright, however, and their huge size makes them more clumsy
than the other races.  Verbeeg make the best warriors of any race, but are
ill-suited for any other profession.

Verbeeg resist heat and cold with nary a mark, due to their huge mass.  However,
their slow minds make them extremely vulnerable to mental attacks.  Verbeeg,
due to their size and stamina, receive the fast healing and bash skills for
free. (Only giant warriors recive bash).

Favored Class: Warrior

Natural Ability: Slam

*************************************
~

0 CYBORG~
The Cyborgs are man-made constucts of man and machine as a symbiote. With only
slightly above average attributes as those of a normal human, the main strength
of a cyborg lies in its ability to train his physical traits far higher than
normally possible due to his inherent nature. Being half machine, cyborgs do
not make good mages or priests, as their mechanical nature somehow make them
less proficient in the use of magicks. Cyborgs do however make natural
warriors and good rogues.
 
Cyborgs can resist poison and the effects thereof due to inbuilt filtration
systems, and are less vulnerable to holy attacks since they are only partly
organic. Unfortunately, the inherent magic in silver and mithril weapons
disrupts their circuitry, and does a great deal more damage than usual.
Electrical damage also tends to hurt cyborgs more, sometimes causing a short-
circuit to happen.

Favored Class: Thief

Natural Ability: Tune, Repair

*************************************
~

0 WOLFEN~
The wolfen are a race of intelligent wolf-like canines who have evolved a
primitive society. Their superior agility makes them ideal thieves, and they
gain the dodge skill automatically. In addition, they are well in tune with the
forces of nature, and make good clerics. Also, having lived in the wilds
for so long, they are familiar with the necessity for survival at any cost, and
can throw themselves into a berserk rage if necessary.
 
However, having only recently achieved sapience, they are not particularly
intelligent, nor versed in the ways of magic, making a wolfen mage a rare sight
indeed.
 
Their animal ancestry gives them two large advantages over humanoids: they have
greatly enhanced night vision, even to the extent of detecting the heat emitted
by warm bodies, and their natural healing rate is higher than most other races.

Favored Class: Thief

Natural Ability: Double benefit from Fast Healing, infravision

*************************************
~

0 HALFLING~
Halflings – also known as Hin, the "quick folk" amongst themselves, or the 
"sly folk" or "good folk" by other races – are a humanoid creatures similar in 
shape to humans. The term "halfling" was derived from the fact that the average 
halfling was around half the size of the average human, but otherwise very 
similar in appearance.

Favored Class: Thief

Natural Ability: Bonus to haggle and steal success

*************************************
~

0 OGRE~
Ogres are a lazy, brutish, avaricious race with notoriously quick tempers.
Their avaricious nature often leads them distrust one another and incite 
squabbling over treasure.

Ogres are gluttonous creatures willing to eat almost anything. They enjoy 
the taste of raw dwarf flesh, but would also eat halfling or elf flesh when they 
could get it. However, now that they have sided with the Humanoid races they find
Goblin to be a reasonable stand-in for halfling. But aren't overly fond of the
taste of other orcish races. They often use the skin and bones of their prey 
to fashion crude loincloths and necklaces

Favored Class: Warrior

Natural Ability: Throw Rock

*************************************
~

