0 TROLL~
Green, huge, and hariy best describes these monstrous beasts.  An average
troll stands roughly nine feet tall, one hundred percent muscle and dirt. 
Born in swamps and raised to kill, Trolls make kick ass berserkers.  Beware
however, more than one pitiful human has fallen to the curse of a wicked
Troll shaman.  

Favored Class: shaman

Natural Ability: Regeneration

*************************************
~

0 DROW~
The drow are dark-skinned humanoid/orcan halfbreeds, the underground
counterparts to the elves.  They are virtually identical to their daylight
cousins, with the only real differences being that the drow are somewhat
more heavily built than normal elves, they have developed superior low-light
vision, and they are adversely affected by sunlight, due to the long period
of adaption that has gone on underground.  See 'help elf' for further
details.  

Favored Class: Knave

Natural Ability: Darkness

*************************************
~

0 URUK-HAI~
The Uruk are without a doubt, the baddest ass orcs to have been bred.  A
stock combination of orc, human, and ogre, the Uruk-hai are a force to be
reckoned with.  From their human ancestors, they have gained intelligence
and wisdom.  From their orc ancestors, they have gained constitution.  And
from their ogre ancestors, strength.  Deeply slanted eyes and sharp tusks
adorn these monstrous beings of muscle and bone.

Favored Class: Berserker

Natural Ability: Bloodlust

*************************************
~

0 HOBGOBLIN~
These thick, twisted relatives of goblins and orcs have an uncanny
ability to see things otherwise hidden from others.  Because hobgoblins make
their home underground, they have developed a keen sense of vision and
garnered some infravision.  They have also become resistant to the hardships
of underground living and become resistant to disease.  
 
Favored Class: Shaman

Natural Ability: Goblin Mob

*************************************
~

0 KOBOLD~
These evil looking guys look like small versions of werewolves.  Razor
sharp fangs more than two inches long decorate the mouth of them, suggesting
a use as an alternative can opener.  

Favored Class: Knave

Natural Ability: Peek, Increase steal chance

*************************************
~

0 STALKER~
These assassins are virtually undetectable, even to their own kind.
They have been known to walk through closed doors into well-attended
dinner parties, slit the throat of the local magistrate, and walk back
out through the wall.
 
Their catlike reflexes and dexterity serve them well, although they
